'''Steven Moreira''' ({{IPA|pt|ˈsti˸.vən mu.ˈɾej.ɾɐ|lang}}<!----The player was born in France. Check for sources if his first name is pronounced in a “Portuguese way” or in a “French way”.---->; born 13 August 1994) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] or [[centre-back]] for [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Columbus Crew]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]].

==Club career==

=== Rennes ===
[[File:Saint-Lô - Rennes CFA2 20160409 - Steven Moreira.JPG|thumb|upright|left|Moreira playing for Rennes B in 2016]]
Moreira first began with AS Champs-sur-Marne in 2000, staying there for five years until he joined US Torcy in 2005.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://actu.fr/sports/football/ligue-2-passe-par-champs-sur-marne-et-torcy-steven-moreira-toulouse-fc-disputera-les-barrages_41899343.html |title=Ligue 2. Passé par Champs-sur-Marne et Torcy, Steven Moreira (Toulouse FC) disputera les barrages |language=fr |author=Rédaction Meaux |publisher=Actu |date=17 May 2021 |access-date=1 September 2024 }}</ref> He later joined the [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]] youth academy in 2009, and secured a professional contract with the Breton side in 2013. While at Rennes, he played both [[Fullback (association football)|full-back]] positions and on the wing at times,<ref>{{Cite news |title=Finale de la Coupe de France Toulouse - Nantes : "J'aurais été content d'avoir Philippe Montanier au TFC", les confidences de l'ancien Violet Steven Moreira |url=https://www.ladepeche.fr/2023/04/26/finale-de-la-coupe-de-france-toulouse-nantes-jaurais-ete-content-davoir-philippe-montanier-au-tfc-les-confidences-de-lancien-violet-steven-moreira-11159843.php |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230426172446/https://www.ladepeche.fr/2023/04/26/finale-de-la-coupe-de-france-toulouse-nantes-jaurais-ete-content-davoir-philippe-montanier-au-tfc-les-confidences-de-lancien-violet-steven-moreira-11159843.php |archive-date=2023-04-26 |access-date=2025-12-10 |work=ladepeche.fr |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2014-12-13 |title=Bastia - Rennes Steven Moreira, homme d'extérieur ? |url=https://www.letelegramme.fr/sports/football/bastia-rennes-steven-moreira-homme-dexterieur-2301965.php |access-date=2025-12-10 |website=Le Télégramme |language=fr-FR}}</ref> making his debut for the club on 11 May 2013 in a [[Ligue 1]] clash.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Valenciennes 4 - 1 Rennes (Ligue 1 12/13) |url=https://rougememoire.com/game/valenciennes-rennes-4-1-2013-5-11 |access-date=2025-12-14 |website=rougememoire.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Valenciennes 4-1 Rennes (May 11, 2013) Lineups |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups/_/gameId/342604 |access-date=2025-12-14 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> In the [[2013-14 Ligue 1|2013–14 season]], he appeared sparingly to start the year, playing in three of the first four games to start the new campaign, before being benched and not appearing for over three months.<ref>{{Cite web |title=2013-2014 Steven Moreira Match Logs |url=https://fbref.com/en/players/f10983ae/matchlogs/2013-2014/Steven-Moreira-Match-Logs |access-date=2025-12-14 |website=FBref.com |language=en}}</ref> He appeared in the [[2014 Coupe de France final|Coupe de France]] final, losing to [[En Avant Guingamp|Guingamp]] 2–0 in a ''[[Derby Breton]].''<ref name=":0" /> He scored his first goal for Rennes on 19 January 2016 in a [[2015–16 Coupe de France|Coupe de France]] match, netting his team's only goal in a 3–1 loss to [[Football Bourg-en-Bresse Péronnas 01|Bourg-en-Bresse]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2016-01-19 |title=Football. Coupe de France : l'exploit de Bourg-en-Bresse |url=https://www.leprogres.fr/football/2016/01/19/coupe-de-france-l-exploit-de-bourg-en-bresse-fbbp01-rennes |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240331211330/https://www.leprogres.fr/football/2016/01/19/coupe-de-france-l-exploit-de-bourg-en-bresse-fbbp01-rennes |archive-date=2024-03-31 |access-date=2024-03-31 |website=www.leprogres.fr |language=FR-fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2013-12-04 |title=Rennes. Steven Moreira signe pro |url=https://www.letelegramme.fr/sports/football/spanrennesspan-steven-moreira-signe-pro-2013843.php |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240331212435/https://www.letelegramme.fr/sports/football/spanrennesspan-steven-moreira-signe-pro-2013843.php |archive-date=2024-03-31 |access-date=2024-03-31 |website=Le Télégramme |language=FR}}</ref>

=== FC Lorient ===
Moreria joined [[FC Lorient]] on 30 August 2016 for a reported [[Euro sign|€]]1.2 million, signing a four-year deal.<ref>{{multiref2|1={{cite news|title=Transfert : Steven Moreira à Lorient/722690|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Transfert-steven-moreira-a-lorient/722690|accessdate=2 September 2016|work=L'Equipe|date=30 August 2016|language=French}}|2={{Cite web |last=Lavaud |first=Thomas |date=2017-05-27 |title=Barrages Ligue 1 - Ligue 2 {{!}} Le FC Lorient sans défense |url=https://www.francebleu.fr/sports/football/barrages-ligue-1-ligue-2-le-fc-lorient-sans-defense-1495893043 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230917225422/https://www.francebleu.fr/sports/football/barrages-ligue-1-ligue-2-le-fc-lorient-sans-defense-1495893043 |archive-date=2023-09-17 |access-date=2023-09-17 |website=ici, par France Bleu et France 3 |language=fr}}}}</ref> After his [[2016–17 Ligue 1|first season]] in Lorient, his side were relegated to [[Ligue 2]]. During the following season, he scored a goal against [[RC Lens]] in the second round of the [[2017–18 Coupe de la Ligue|Coupe de la Ligue]] in August 2017,<ref>{{Cite web |date=29 October 2022 |title=Lorient vs. Lens Match Report – Tuesday August 22, 2017 |url=https://fbref.com/en/matches/de2d1104/Lorient-Lens-August-22-2017-Coupe-de-la-Ligue |access-date=29 October 2022 |website=FB Ref}}</ref> and on 29 January 2018 scored the only goal in a victory versus eventual Ligue 2 [[2017–18 Ligue 2|champions]] [[Stade de Reims|Reims]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-06-26 |title=Steven MOREIRA |url=https://www.fclorient.bzh/joueur/steven-moreira/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230626000252/https://fclweb.fr/joueur/steven-moreira/ |archive-date=2023-06-26 |access-date=2024-12-06 |website=FC Lorient |language=fr}}</ref> He moved to [[Centre-back|central defense]] in a game against [[AS Nancy Lorraine|Nancy]] late in the season, remaining at that position for two months, before returning to right-back. Manager [[Mickaël Landreau]] later explained the decision was designed “to establish his leadership,” believing the role allowed those qualities to come through more clearly.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2018-03-04 |title=Steven Moreira a passé le test avec succès |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/bretagne/finistere/steven-moreira-passe-le-test-avec-succes-5605387 |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20251220101529/https://www.ouest-france.fr/bretagne/finistere/steven-moreira-passe-le-test-avec-succes-5605387 |archive-date=2025-12-20 |access-date=2025-12-20 |work=Ouest-France.fr |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=2018-04-05 |title=FC Lorient. Moreira revient épauler les Merlus |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/fc-lorient/fc-lorient-moreira-revient-epauler-les-merlus-5675685 |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20251220102941/https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/fc-lorient/fc-lorient-moreira-revient-epauler-les-merlus-5675685 |archive-date=2025-12-20 |access-date=2025-12-20 |work=Ouest-France.fr |language=fr-FR}}</ref>

=== Toulouse ===
After two years in at Lorient, Moreira was transferred to Ligue 1 side [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]] on 10 August 2018 and agreed to terms on a three-year deal.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Journal du Mercato : ça s'agite dans tous les sens au Real Madrid ! |url=https://www.footmercato.net/a4735152827300027440-journal-du-mercato-ca-sagite-dans-tous-les-sens-au-real-madrid |access-date=2022-10-29 |website=Foot Mercato : Info Transferts Football - Actu Foot Transfert |date=10 August 2018 |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-10-29 |title=Mercato : Steven Moreira signe au Toulouse Football Club, un contrat proposé à Stéphane Mbia {{!}} Actu Toulouse (in French) |url=https://actu.fr/occitanie/toulouse_31555/mercato-steven-moreira-signe-toulouse-football-club-contrat-propose-stephane-mbia_18143212.html |access-date=2022-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221029231147/https://actu.fr/occitanie/toulouse_31555/mercato-steven-moreira-signe-toulouse-football-club-contrat-propose-stephane-mbia_18143212.html |archive-date=29 October 2022 }}</ref> His first year with Toulouse was forgettable, as he appeared in just 14 matches across all competitions, with his only win coming in the [[Coupe de France]] match against [[OGC Nice|Nice]]. During the [[2019–20 Ligue 1|2019–20 season]], he incurred a three-match suspension following a red card received during a match against [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] on 24 November 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2019-12-02 |title=Commission de discipline : les décisions du 27 novembre 2019 - LFP.fr |url=https://www.lfp.fr/corporate/article/commission-de-discipline-les-decisions-du-27-novembre-2019.htm |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191202205317/https://www.lfp.fr/corporate/article/commission-de-discipline-les-decisions-du-27-novembre-2019.htm |archive-date=2019-12-02 |access-date=2023-09-17 |website=lfp.fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2019-11-24 |title=Toulouse v Marseille {{!}} 24 novembre 2019 {{!}} Goal.com Français |url=https://www.goal.com/fr/match/toulouse-vs-marseille/6c5e3dy75uzs7axojzrma6oa2 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230917230734/https://www.goal.com/fr/match/toulouse-vs-marseille/6c5e3dy75uzs7axojzrma6oa2 |archive-date=2023-09-17 |access-date=2023-09-17 |website=www.goal.com |language=fr}}</ref> On 15 February 2020, he was shown a red card for a foul on [[Adam Ounas]], resulting in another three-match suspension.<ref>{{multiref2|1={{Cite web |date=2020-02-15 |title=Toulouse 0-2 Nice (Feb 15, 2020) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/541990 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230917231742/https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/541990 |archive-date=2023-09-17 |access-date=2023-09-17 |website=ESPN |language=en}}|2={{Cite web |last=Berthaud |first=Alexandre |date=2020-02-19 |title=Le TFC privé de son latéral droit pendant trois matchs |url=https://www.francebleu.fr/sports/football/le-tfc-prive-de-son-lateral-droit-pendant-trois-matchs-1582146418 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230917225030/https://www.francebleu.fr/sports/football/ligue-1-reduits-a-9-contre-11-les-toulousains-s-inclinent-face-a-nice-au-bout-d-un-match-fou-0-2-1581801315 |archive-date=2023-09-17 |access-date=2023-09-17 |website=ici, par France Bleu et France 3 |language=fr}}|3={{Cite web |date=2020-02-19 |title=Deux suspendus à Toulouse |url=https://www.ligue1.fr/Articles/Actu/2020/02/19/deux-suspendus-toulouse |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230917233239/https://www.ligue1.fr/Articles/ACTU/2020/02/19/deux-suspendus-toulouse |archive-date=2023-09-17 |access-date=2023-09-17 |website=Ligue1 |language=fr-FR}}}}</ref> At the conclusion of the season, his side were relegated to Ligue 2. After missing the first four games of the [[2020–21 Ligue 2|2020–21]] season due to [[COVID-19]], He would score his only goal for the club on 26 September 2020, coming on as a second-half substitute and contributing to a 3–1 victory at home for ''Les Violets.''<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-09-26 |title=Enfin! |url=https://www.toulousefc.com/fr/enfin-0 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230917234842/https://www.toulousefc.com/fr/enfin-0 |archive-date=2023-09-17 |access-date=2023-09-17 |website=ToulouseFC |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Ligue 2. Steven Moreira, joueur du Toulouse FC : "Une osmose s'est créée au sein du groupe" |url=https://www.ladepeche.fr/2020/12/04/steven-moreira-une-osmose-sest-creee-au-sein-du-groupe-9237277.php |url-access=subscription |access-date=2025-12-20 |website=ladepeche.fr |language=fr}}</ref> On 20 March 2021, Moreira received a red card in a 1–0 defeat against [[Chamois Niortais F.C.|Niort]], serving a three-match suspension as a result.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-03-20 |title=Feuille de match |url=https://www.ligue2.fr/feuille-match |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230917234039/https://www.ligue2.fr/feuille-match?matchId=68765 |archive-date=2023-09-17 |access-date=2023-09-17 |website=Ligue2 |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-04-15 |title=Steven Moreira, suspension terminée |url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/steven-moreira-suspension-terminee,57439.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230917235625/https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/steven-moreira-suspension-terminee,57439.html |archive-date=2023-09-17 |access-date=2023-09-17 |website=www.lesviolets.com |language=fr}}</ref>

=== Columbus Crew ===
[[File:Steven Moreira NYCFC v Columbus 10 May 2026-137.jpg|thumb|upright|Moreira with the [[Columbus Crew]] in 2026]]
In August 2021, Moreira signed with [[Columbus Crew]] in [[Major League Soccer]] on a free transfer until the end of the 2021 season, with team options to extend his contract until the end of the 2023 season.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.columbuscrew.com/news/columbus-crew-signs-french-defender-steven-moreira|title=Columbus Crew signs French defender Steven Moreira &#124; Columbus Crew|website=ColumbusCrew.com}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web |last=Chirat |first=Antoine |date=2024-01-03 |title=EXCLU - Steven Moreira : « Messi n'a pas de MLS, mais moi oui ! » |url=https://www.onzemondial.com/autres-championnats/exclu-steven-moreira-messi-n-a-pas-de-mls-mais-moi-oui-866356 |access-date=2025-05-07 |website=Onze Mondial |language=fr}}</ref> He would go on to appear in eight total matches in his first season, including making his team debut in the [[2021 Campeones Cup|Campeones Cup]] victory versus [[Cruz Azul]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Myers |first=Jacob |date=2021-09-29 |title=Columbus Crew wins Campeones Cup, shuts out Liga MX's Cruz Azul |url=https://www.dispatch.com/story/sports/2021/09/29/columbus-crew-wins-campeones-cup-shuts-out-liga-mxs-cruz-azul/5923588001/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230625234848/https://www.dispatch.com/story/sports/2021/09/29/columbus-crew-wins-campeones-cup-shuts-out-liga-mxs-cruz-azul/5923588001/ |archive-date=2023-06-25 |access-date=2023-06-25 |website=The Columbus Dispatch |language=en-US}}</ref> On 27 August 2022, Moreira scored his first goal for the Crew, a right-footed volley in the 96th minute to tie [[Hell Is Real derby|Hell is Real]] rivals [[FC Cincinnati]] 2–2.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-10-29 |title=Columbus Crew tie at FC Cincinnati on late Moreira goal |url=https://www.dispatch.com/story/sports/mls/columbus-crew/2022/08/28/columbus-crew-tie-at-fc-cincinnati-on-late-moreira-goal/65457928007/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221029221313/https://www.dispatch.com/story/sports/mls/columbus-crew/2022/08/28/columbus-crew-tie-at-fc-cincinnati-on-late-moreira-goal/65457928007/ |archive-date=2022-10-29  |access-date=2022-10-29 }}</ref> During the 2023 season, Moreira became a key contributor at centre-back for a Columbus side that won [[MLS Cup 2023|MLS Cup]] 3–1 against [[Los Angeles FC]]. Described as having a "unique role",<ref>{{Cite web |last=Boehm |first=Charles |date=Jul 12, 2024 |title=Bouanga & Moreira: The friendship behind LAFC vs. Columbus Crew |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/bouanga-moreira-the-friendship-behind-lafc-vs-columbus-crew |access-date=2025-05-07 |website=mlssoccer |language=en}}</ref> he was given the freedom to carry the ball high into the midfield or make line-splitting passes.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Lowery |first=Joseph |date=Feb 19, 2024 |title=One MLS star to follow at each position in 2024 |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/must-watch-one-mls-star-to-follow-at-each-position-in-2024 |access-date=2025-05-07 |website=mlssoccer |language=en}}</ref> After the final, it was announced that he extended his contract until 2025, with an option for 2026.<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Rudy-camacho-et-steven-moreira-prolongent-au-columbus-crew-en-mls/1436608 |title=Rudy Camacho et Steven Moreira prolongent au Columbus Crew en MLS |language=fr |publisher=L'Equipe |date=12 December 2023 |access-date=1 September 2024}}</ref>

Moreira's 2024 season began with regular appearances in the starting eleven, including starting all matches and playing every minute in the [[CONCACAF Champions Cup]] through the [[2024 CONCACAF Champions Cup|final]], where Columbus were beaten 3–0 by [[C.F. Pachuca|Pachuca]] at [[Estadio Hidalgo]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-06-01 |title=Pachuca defeats Columbus Crew for sixth Concacaf Champions Cup |url=https://www.concacaf.com/champions-league/news/pachuca-defeats-columbus-crew-for-sixth-concacaf-champions-cup/ |access-date=2025-12-14 |website=Concacaf |language=en}}</ref> He scored his first goal of the season with a 30-yard shot in a 2–2 home draw to the [[Portland Timbers]] on 20 April.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=2024-04-21 |title=Cucho, Moreira score goals to help Crew play Timbers to tie |url=https://www.tsn.ca/soccer/cucho-hernandez-steven-moreira-score-goals-to-help-columbus-crew-play-portland-timbers-to-tie-1.2107368 |access-date=2025-12-14 |website=TSN |language=en}}</ref> Moreira made his 100th appearance across all competitions for the club on 15 May.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Steven Moreira Stats {{!}} Soccerway |url=https://www.soccerway.com/player/moreira-steven/zk4qsEuM/ |access-date=2025-12-14 |website=www.soccerway.com |language=en}}</ref> During the [[2024 Leagues Cup|Leagues Cup]], Moreira once again started every match and played every minute for Columbus, as they went on to win the tournament, defeating Los Angeles FC in the [[2024 Leagues Cup final|final]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |title=CLBvsLAFC 08-25-2024 {{!}} Match Recap |url=https://www.leaguescup.com/competitions/leagues-cup/2024/matches/clbvslafc-08-25-2024/ |access-date=2025-12-14 |website=leaguescup |language=en}}</ref> An ankle injury would keep Moreira out of the final three games of the regular season,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mac Kay |first=Brianna |title=Columbus Crew could have to go without a backup goalkeeper after 5 international call-ups |url=https://www.dispatch.com/story/sports/mls/columbus-crew/2024/10/07/5-columbus-crew-players-called-up-during-fifa-international-window/75511777007/ |access-date=2025-12-14 |website=The Columbus Dispatch |language=en-US}}</ref> as Columbus finished with a club-record 66 points but were eliminated from the [[2024 MLS Cup playoffs|playoffs]] in the first round by the [[New York Red Bulls]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |title=By The Numbers {{!}} Crew host Revs in home finale {{!}} Columbus Crew |url=https://www.columbuscrew.com/news/by-the-numbers-crew-host-revs-in-home-finale |access-date=2025-12-14 |website=ColumbusCrew.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last= |title=New York Red Bulls defy odds to deny Columbus Crew repeat: "The season is not over" {{!}} MLSSoccer.com |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/new-york-red-bulls-defy-odds-to-deny-columbus-crew-repeat-the-season-is-not-over |access-date=2025-12-14 |website=mlssoccer |language=en}}</ref> Moreira ended the season with 42 appearances across all competitions, and was named Major League Soccer Defender of the Year and on the Best XI.<ref>{{multiref2 
|1={{Cite web |last= |title=Columbus Crew's Steven Moreira named 2024 MLS Defender of the Year {{!}} Columbus Crew |url=https://www.columbuscrew.com/news/columbus-crew-s-steven-moreira-named-2024-mls-defender-of-the-year-x0718 |access-date=2025-12-14 |website=ColumbusCrew.com |language=en}}
|2={{Cite web |last= |title=2024 MLS Best XI presented by Continental Tire|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/2024-mls-best-xi-presented-by-continental-tire |access-date=2025-12-14 |website=mlssoccer |language=en}}
|3={{Cite web |last= |title=Columbus Crew: What we learned in 2024 & what comes next {{!}} MLSSoccer.com |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/columbus-crew-what-we-learned-in-2024-season-what-comes-next |access-date=2025-12-14 |website=mlssoccer |language=en}}}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in France, Moreira is of Cape Verdean descent, and is a former France youth international. He played at the [[2013 UEFA European Under-19 Championship|2013 UEFA European Under-19 European Championship]], finishing as the runner-up.<ref name=":0" /> He was called up to the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]] for a set of friendlies in October 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dispatch.com/story/sports/mls/columbus-crew/2023/10/09/columbus-crew-steven-moreira-has-first-fifa-international-window-call-up-cape-verde-islands/71122202007/|title=Columbus Crew defender Steven Moreira called up to represent Cape Verde Islands|website=The Columbus Dispatch}}</ref> He debuted with Cape Verde in a 5–1 loss to [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] on 12 October 2023.<ref name="INFORPRESS – Agência Cabo-Verdiana de Notícias 2023 u157">{{cite web | title=Futebol: Cabo Verde goleado pela Argélia no dia em que conhece adversários do CAN'2023 – INFORPRESS | website=INFORPRESS – Agência Cabo-Verdiana de Notícias | date=2023-10-12 | url=https://inforpress.cv/futebol-cabo-verde-goleado-pela-argelia-no-dia-em-que-conhece-adversarios-do-can2023/ | language=pt | access-date=2023-10-13}}</ref> Moreira was part of the Cape Verde team that made the quarter-finals of the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-01-07 |title=Profile of Cape Verde Islands team for 2023 Africa Cup of Nations |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/profile-cape-verde-islands-team-2023-africa-cup-nations-2024-01-08/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240219182630/https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/profile-cape-verde-islands-team-2023-africa-cup-nations-2024-01-08/ |archive-date=2024-02-19 |access-date=2024-02-19 |website=Reuters.com}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
Moreira has mainly been deployed as an attacking right-back in his career, and has been noted for his intelligence, [[Cross (association football)|crossing]] ability and calmness under pressure.<ref>{{multiref2
|1={{Cite news |title=Steven MOREIRA - FC Lorient |url=https://fclweb.fr/joueur/steven-moreira/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230626000252/https://fclweb.fr/joueur/steven-moreira/ |archive-date=2023-06-26 |access-date=2025-12-10 |work=FC Lorient |language=fr-FR}}|2={{Cite news |title=Nouvelle génération, nouveaux visages |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Nouvelle-generation-nouveaux-visages/545478 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221029224552/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Nouvelle-generation-nouveaux-visages/545478 |archive-date=2022-10-29 |access-date=2025-12-10 |work=L'Équipe |language=fr-FR}}|3={{Cite web |last=Johnson |first=Bailey |title=Columbus Crew's Steven Moreira challenged by coach Wilfried Nancy to learn new position |url=https://www.dispatch.com/story/sports/mls/columbus-crew/2023/02/03/steven-moreira-crew-right-back-learning-to-play-center-back/69865840007/ |access-date=2025-12-10 |website=The Columbus Dispatch |language=en-US}}|4={{Cite web |title=Steven Moreira, l'ambitieux latéral qui doit se faire une place |url=https://www.ladepeche.fr/article/2018/08/16/2852142-steven-moreira-ambitieux-lateral-doit-faire-place.html |access-date=2025-12-20 |website=ladepeche.fr |language=fr}}}}</ref> Since 2023, he has shifted to a right-sided centre-back in a back three. Speaking about the change, Moreira said: "I no longer play in my position, which was right-back. I play as a defender in a three-man defense and I have incredible freedom. I find myself almost often in front of goal."<ref name=":1" />

== Personal life ==
Moreira is [[Muslim]] and fasts during the month of [[Ramadan]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Boehm |first=Charles |date=Apr 7, 2023 |title=Respecting Ramadan in MLS: "Spiritually it gives you strength to keep going" {{!}} MLSSoccer.com |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/respecting-ramadan-in-mls-spiritually-it-gives-you-strength-to-keep-going |access-date=2025-02-28 |website=mlssoccer |language=en}}</ref>

